@usernamesreprise9417 Thanks for that. To clarify top army ranking historically the correct title was Sergeant Major General hence it is below a Lieutenant General.
Also in WW2 Michael Calvert (Mad Mike) reached the rank of Brigadier at 29. Jack Profumo MP was similar although he blotted his copy book & was ridiculed as only going to bed for the exercise!
However pride of place must be with Roland Boys Bradford from Witton Park, Co. Durham who attained the rank of Brigadier at the unbelievable age of only 25.

